Biggest and Wildest Cacti: The Sonoran Desert

Nature Documentary hosted by Laura Post, published by NHK broadcasted as part of NHK Great Nature series in 2012 - English narration
 <a href="
http://docuwiki.net/images/9/96/Biggest-and-Wildest-Cacti-The-Sonoran-Desert-Cover.jpg" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
http://docuwiki.net/images/9/96/Biggest-and-Wildest-Cacti-The-Sonoran-Desert-Cover.jpg</a>

Information
------------------------------

The red-hot vastness of the Sonoran Desert of North America is the habitat of a surprising number of life forms. A high-definition camera travels deep into the "cactus desert" in search of them.
